cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper studies the computational complexity of strategic voting in multiwinner elections, which is a classic topic in game theory. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the problem of selecting the best candidates, which is a common task in AI applications such as recommendation systems and personnel selection. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper analyzes the computational complexity of various tie-breaking mechanisms and group evaluation functions, which are algorithmic components of the shortlisting process. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the trade-off between egalitarian and utilitarian group evaluation functions, which is a common theme in fairness-aware machine learning. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses mathematical models and proofs to establish the computational complexity of strategic voting in shortlisting.
